'''Shilpa Shetty''' ([[Tulu language|Tulu]]: {{lang|kn|<U+0CB6><U+0CBF><U+0CB2><U+0CCD><U+0CAA><U+0CBE> <U+0CB6><U+0CC6><U+0C9F><U+0CCD><U+0C9F><U+0CBF>}}; born 8 June 1975) is an [[Cinema of India|Indian film]] [[actress]] and [[Model (person)|model]]. Since making her debut in the film ''[[Baazigar]]'' (1993), she has appeared in nearly 40 [[Bollywood]], [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]], [[Cinema of Andhra Pradesh|Telugu]] and [[Cinema of Karnataka|Kannada films]], her first leading role being in the 1994 ''[[Aag (1994 film)|Aag]]''. Although she has been through years of decline during her career, Shetty has been willing to reinvent herself quite often. Her performances in ''[[Dhadkan]]'' (2000) and ''[[Rishtey]]'' (2002) were appreciated, while her portrayal of an AIDS patient in ''[[Phir Milenge]]'' (2004) won her many accolades. Her younger sister [[Shamita Shetty]] is also a [[Bollywood]] film actress. Shilpa is currently judging a reality show "Zara Nachke Dikha" along with two other judges Arshad Warsi and Vaibhavi Merchant aired in Starplus.

Shetty has been embroiled in various controversies including suspected [[Shilpa Shetty#Alleged mafia links|mafia links]]. In 2006 she was issued with a [[writ|warrant]] on charges of [[obscenity]]. After taking part in the British ''[[Celebrity Big Brother 2007 (UK)|Celebrity Big Brother]]'' TV show in 2007, Shetty was crowned the winner with 63% of the final vote,<ref>{{cite web
| work=channel4.com | title=Shilpa Shetty wins Celebrity Big Brother 2007 | url=http://www.channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1456&housemateId=9 | accessdate=28 January 2007}}</ref> after an international [[Celebrity Big Brother racism controversy|racism controversy]] involving her and fellow contestants [[Jade Goody]], [[Jo O'Meara]] and [[Danielle Lloyd]]. This was followed by a re-establishment of her status in the film industry in 2007 when she appeared in two successive movies, ''[[Life in a... Metro]]'' and ''[[Apne]]'', with her performance in the former drawing positive reviews.<ref>{{cite web | author=Sen, Raja | work=Rediff.com | title=The most powerful actresses of 2007 | url=http://specials.rediff.com/yearend/2007/dec/18yrpoweractress11.htm | accessdate=29 December 2007}}</ref>

==Biography==
Shilpa Shetty was born in a traditional close-knit family in [[Mangalore]]<ref name="timesmama">{{cite news | work=timesonline.co.uk
| title=Times exclusive: interview with Shilpa Shetty's mother | url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/asia/article1294040.ece | accessdate=27 February 2007 | location=London | first=Ashling | last=Oconnor | date=18 January 2007}}</ref> that hails from the [[Bunt (community)|Bunt]] community.<ref name="birth">{{cite news
|url=http://www.expressindia.com/news/fullstory.php?newsid=89656
|title=Now meet Dr Shilpa Shetty
|publisher=[[Express India]]
|work=Indian Express Newspapers (Mumbai)
|date=2007-07-18
|accessdate=2009-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | work=inhome.rediff.com | title=Will Big Brother boost Shilpa's career? | url=http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/18shilpa.htm | accessdate=19 January 2007}}</ref>

She is the eldest daughter of Surendra and Sunanda Shetty, [[Manufacturing|manufacturers]] of tamper-proof caps for the [[pharmaceutical]] industry,<ref name="timesmama"/> and her native language is [[Tulu language|Tulu]] although she speaks several other languages at differing levels, including English, [[Kannada]], [[Marathi]], [[Hindi]], [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Gujarati language|Gujarati]], [[Telugu language|Telugu]], [[Urdu]] and basic [[French language|French]].<ref name="Shilpa Shetty official site biography">{{cite web | work=shilpa-shetty.com| title=Shilpa Shetty Biography - by: Dechen| url=http://www.shilpa-shetty.com/biography.html| accessdate=20 October 2007}}</ref>

In [[Mumbai]], she attended St. Anthony Girls' High School in [[Chembur]], and later attended [[Ramniranjan Anandilal Podar College of Commerce & Economics|Podar College]] in [[Matunga]]. A trained [[Bharatanatyam]] dancer, she is also into sports, was the captain of the volleyball team in school, has earned a [[Black belt (martial arts)|black belt]] in [[karate]] and is currently a dancesport expert and enthusiast.<ref>{{cite web | work=channel4.com | title=C4 Profile | url=http://www.channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/housemates/housemate_news.jsp?id=9 | accessdate=19 January 2007}}</ref>

Shetty's younger sister [[Shamita Shetty]] is also a [[Bollywood]] actress. They worked together once in the film ''[[Fareb]]'' (2005).

At 5&nbsp;ft 10&nbsp;inches (178&nbsp;cm), Shilpa Shetty is among the tallest actresses in Bollywood. It was revealed on 29 March 2009 that Shilpa had purchased a house on [[St. George's Hill]] in [[Surrey]], England with her husband Raj Kundra.<ref name="uk.news.yahoo.com">http://uk.news.yahoo.com/21/20090329/ten-shetty-aims-for-british-tv-fame-5f8abb3.html</ref>

==Career==
===Film career===
[[Image:Shilpa Shetty backstage.jpg|200px|thumb|right|Shetty at the Miss Bollywood-The musical]]
Shetty started her career by modelling for [[Limca]] in 1991 at age 16,<ref>{{cite web|work=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|title=Shilpa denies any underworld connection|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/48771.cms|accessdate=3 January 2007}}</ref> and made her film debut in 1993 with ''[[Baazigar]]'', portraying a woman murdered by her [[Psychopathy|psychopathic]] boyfriend. Shetty took the supporting role of Seema, co-starring alongside [[Shahrukh Khan]] and [[Kajol]]; the film was a major success and earned her a nomination for [[Filmfare Best Supporting Actress Award]].<ref>{{cite web|work=filmfareawards.indiatimes.com|title=Filmfare nomination for Shetty|url=http://filmfareawards.indiatimes.com/articleshow/articleshow/368610.cms|accessdate=23 January 2007}}</ref>

Her first leading role was in the film ''[[Aag (1994 film)|Aag]]'' in 1994, which was averagely received at the box office. She had a hit that same year with the film ''[[Main Khiladi Tu Anari]]'' opposite [[Akshay Kumar]].<ref>{{cite web
| work=boxofficeindia.com
| title=Box office analysis
| url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/1994.htm
| accessdate=23 January 2007 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20061206183759/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/1994.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 6 December 2006}}</ref> This was followed by many films which were average to poor performers at the box office. Shetty starred in another big film that year, ''[[Aao Pyaar Karen]]'', followed in 1995 by ''[[Hathkadi]]'', where she was working alongside actors such as [[Saif Ali Khan]], [[Govinda (actor)|Govinda]] and [[Madhoo]], but they failed at the box office. 1997 was one of her busiest years: she appeared in six different films, beginning with the [[Telugu language]] film ''Veedeva Dani Babu''. Her first major Bollywood film of that year was the action thriller ''[[Auzaar]]''. Shilpa portrayed the character of Prathna Thakur alongside actors [[Salman Khan]] and [[Sanjay Kapoor]]. In 1998, she had one release, ''[[Pardesi Babu]]'', for which she received critical acclaim and won the [[Bollywood Movie Awards|Bollywood Movie Award]] for ''Best Supporting Actress''.
In 2000, Shetty received much acclaim for her role in ''[[Dhadkan]]'' which earned reasonable takings at the Indian box office.<ref>{{cite web
| work=boxofficeindia.com
| title=Box office analysis
| url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/2000.htm.asp
| accessdate=23 January 2007}} {{Dead link|date=September 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> She received several nominations under the Best Actress category in different award ceremonies. She would later go on to star with [[Anil Kapoor]] and [[Karisma Kapoor]] in the film ''[[Rishtey]]'' (2002). Her comic performance as an eccentric fisherwoman was appreciated and she received a nomination under the [[Filmfare Best Supporting Actress Award]] category and various nominations for Best Comedian as well.<ref>{{cite web
| work=filmfareawards.indiatimes.com
| title=Filmfare nomination for Shetty
| url=http://filmfareawards.indiatimes.com/articleshow/articleshow/368744.cms
| accessdate=23 January 2007}}</ref>

2004 was also a good year for Shetty with the release of ''[[Garv: Pride and Honour|Garv]]'' in which she portrayed a [[Muslim]] orphan and disillusioned [[table dance]]r starring opposite [[Salman Khan]]. According to Shetty, she chose to do the film because she liked the subject. The film was a [[cop drama]].<ref name="rediffheart"/> However, she received much acclaim for her performance in ''[[Phir Milenge]]'', where she made a sensitive portrayal of a successful city high-flyer who contracts [[HIV]] via [[unprotected sex]] and becomes a [[social stigma|social outcast]] as a result. The film, based on 1993's ''[[Philadelphia (film)|Philadelphia]]'', was perceived to have tackled a [[Taboo|social taboo]] as yet unaddressed by Bollywood.<ref name="bbcprofile"/> The film earned Shetty a Filmfare Best Actress nomination, and provided an impetus for her HIV-related charity work ([[Shilpa Shetty#HIV-AIDS|see below]]). Film critic [[Taran Adarsh]] from ''[[indiaFM]]'' noted, "Phir Milenge belongs to Shilpa Shetty completely. She delivers, what can be rightly called, the performance of her career. The viewer feels and empathizes with the character mainly because of her effective portrayal. She conveys the pain and the emotional upheaval through her expressive eyes, making it amongst the most memorable performances the year has seen so far."<ref>{{cite web
| work=indiafm.com
| title=Shetty shines in Phir Milenge
| url=http://www.indiafm.com/movies/review/7176/index.html
| accessdate=23 January 2007}}</ref>
This marked a break from the previous trend of superficial song-and-dance items in favour of roles which have a greater depth of character,<ref name="rediffheart"/> exemplified by her film ''[[Dus]]'' (2005), an action thriller. Although it received average returns at the box office,<ref>{{cite web
| work=boxofficeindia.com
| title=Box office analysis
| url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/2005.htm
| accessdate=23 January 2007 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070120111710/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/2005.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 20 January 2007}}</ref> Shetty stated that she had taken the role in order to reinvent herself by portraying the rather unconventional character of an anti-terrorist squad member.<ref name="rediffheart"/> She also starred with her sister in the film ''Fareb'' in 2005. Shilpa had one release in 2006, the much delayed ''[[Shaadi Karke Phas Gaya Yaar]]''. The film was a box office flop, but she got good reviews for her role as a not entirely likeable wife.<ref>{{cite web
| work=indiafm.com
| title=Shaadi Karke Phas Gaya Yaar
| url=http://www.indiafm.com/movies/review/11637/index.html
| accessdate=25 January 2007}}</ref> In 2006, she was a judge on ''Jhalak Dikhlaja'', a [[Sony Entertainment Television (India)|Sony Entertainment Television]] dance show based on the original UK show ''[[Strictly Come Dancing]]''.

Shetty was once featured in [[Mani Ratnam|Mani Ratnam's]] stage show, [[Netru, Indru, Naalai]].

2007 proved to be Shetty's most successful year at the box office so far. Her first release, ''[[Life In A... Metro]]'', won a significant reception, and became the first Bollywood movie to premiere at [[Leicester Square]].<ref>{{cite web | work=Ibnlive.com | title=Shilpa's World Premiere in London | url=http://www.ibnlive.com/news/showbiz/05_2007/pics-shilpas-big-day-in-london-40046.html | accessdate=1 July 2007}}</ref>
The film performed well at the box office, and was declared a semi-hit within three weeks. Additionally, the film was critically acclaimed and Shetty's performance was appreciated, with [[Rajeev Masand]] of [[CNN-IBN]] writing, "It's a terrific performance and unquestionably Shilpa's best to date."<ref>{{cite web|author=Masand, Rajeev|work=Ibnlive.com| title=Masand's verdict: Metro|url=http://www.ibnlive.com/news/masands-verdict-metro/40402-8-p1.html|accessdate=29 December 2007}}</ref> Her second release, alongside three Deols, [[Dharmendra]], [[Sunny Deol|Sunny]] and [[Bobby Deol|Bobby]], the drama ''[[Apne]]'', was also a box office success.

===Celebrity Big Brother 2007===
Shetty was a contestant in and the winner of ''[[Celebrity Big Brother 2007 (UK)|Celebrity Big Brother UK]]''.<ref name="BB7">{{cite web
| work=metro.co.uk
| title=Bollywood star in Celebrity Big Brother
